== Current main differences vs zuyu reference ==
- ruzu logs richer Rust-side state (`current_core`, `affinity`, `ThreadState`) but not the same raw `SVC_IN/SVC_OUT` formatter as zuyu.
- The first worker starts on core 1, which matches the important upstream handoff.
- The second worker path diverges in shape:
  - zuyu reference shows the main thread sleeping immediately after the second worker bootstrap window
  - ruzu currently shows the second worker entering `svc=0x1c` on core 1 in the comparable focused trace
- ruzu currently shows several workers entering `WAITING` immediately at `StartThread` where the compact zuyu reference emphasizes successful start plus later execution on target core.

== What to compare against ==
- CreateThread/StartThread cadence around `PC=0x01D31B18`
- first handoff to core 1 after the first worker starts
- `SignalProcessWideKey` immediately following `StartThread`
- whether the second worker bootstrap is followed by the same sleep/wait cadence as the zuyu reference
